<subSubSection pageId="61" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="61.[151,1437,1117,1252]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
This genus is well defined by the characters given in the key (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[893,1083,1117,1143]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Wei, M. - C." box="[1139,1396,1117,1143]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="53 - 74" refId="ref79164" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Wei, M. - C. (2012) Pamphiliid sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) of Mt. Yunshan, Hunan Province, China. Memoirs of the National Museum of Nature and Science, Tokyo, 48, 53 - 74." type="journal article" year="2012">Shinohara &amp; Wei 2012</bibRefCitation>
for more details). Besides the 
<typeStatus box="[454,502,1154,1180]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Takeuchi" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[607,791,1153,1180]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cornaceae" genus="Cornus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cornales" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leucocephala">
<emphasis box="[607,791,1153,1180]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">C. leucocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, only one species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara, 2012" authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="2012" box="[1011,1369,1153,1180]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Crataegus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="yunshanica">
<emphasis box="[1011,1173,1153,1180]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">C. yunshanica</emphasis>
Shinohara, 2012
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingRegion box="[151,336,1189,1216]" country="China" name="Hunan" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Hunan Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[350,420,1189,1215]" name="China" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">China</collectingCountry>
, is known. A postulated autapomorphy of this genus is the absence of the basal preapical spur of the hind tibia (
<figureCitation box="[400,469,1225,1251]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-26@38.[164,1422,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 2. Key to tribes and genera 2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876497/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: 2b, c). The host plants and immature stages are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
